metadata.name: Miniscapes #39
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: RAUSCH #186
metadata.description:
RAUSCH is a series of generative artworks that explore imaginary digital architectures. 

This series challenges traditional notions of architectural representation and raises important questions about the role of resolution in design. Just as the pixel resolution of an image affects its perceived quality, the resolution of an architectural space can affect its qualities and livability. By embracing digital variation through codes, this series explores the interplay between abstract and concrete space through multiple resolutions. 

RAUSCH is inspired by the feeling of being overwhelmed by complex, chaotic and messy sensations, and aims to engage the viewer through a sense of wonder, disorientation, and awe.

Released on the occasion of Companions of Code, a group exhibition by VerticalCrypto Art at The NFT Gallery in London. 
Curated by Micol Ap. Exhibition 10-24 February 2023

metadata.name: Contraformas #24
metadata.description:
Shapes are drawn on a space-filling grid against other shapes, using a random walk algorithm. then they are separated with a random offset, hence the name counterforms (contraformas).

created by @mdollinger with p5js

metadata.name: Badgirs City #126
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Broken Angles #26
metadata.description:
Angles represent the artist's view of the space and the visible subject, and the position is chosen so that the audience is able to see the subject from that angle.
The angles determine the audience's point of view in this way and by changing the angles, the audience can see the subject of the image from a new perspective.
Made by p5.js
s = save

metadata.name: Algoscapes | Rock-face #683
metadata.description:
Algoscapes | Rock-face is part of the live outdoor art installation - 'Computational Convergence' at India Art Fair, held from 9-12 February 2023 in New Delhi.

Algoscapes is an ongoing study in fostering an aesthetic of abstraction in landscapes through geometry and code. This piece builds on past work on generating abstract landscapes algorithmically. It is an attempt to capture the essence of naturally occurring rock-faces, to capture the diverse vocabularies ranging from the jagged edges of a mountain's summit to the flowing lines of a canyon wall. The result is a constantly evolving display of color and form, abstract yet reminiscent of the intricacies of the natural world.

'S' key to Save image. '1' and '2' keys for higher resolution images.

Karthik Dondeti (Twitter : @d0ndeti, Instagram : @karthik.dondeti)
Built with p5js.
Feb 2023

metadata.name: KAKOFONI ORQUESTRA #6
metadata.description:
Check the fxhash article to read about the creative process behind it.

Click on the screen to start the music.

Keyboard commands:
1 - turn on/off the track 1
2 - turn on/off the track 1 reverb
3 - turn on/off the track 2
4 - turn on/off the track 2 reverb

I strongly recommend reloading the piece after 15 minutes (or a full play of the song), as the effects are time-related and can get lost after a long time.
The implemented features refer to the values of Hydra's brightness, contrast and modulation functions, with the lowest value being the rarest.
The way the song is performed changes every time you click on the screen.

Designed for Desktop/Notebook computers on Google Chrome Version 104.0.5112.102 (64 bits)

metadata.name: Archiplex II #18
metadata.description: Archiplex II lays its foundations on Brutalist and Bauhaus design. Through simple, triangular shapes and hand-picked, bold colour palettes, this long-form series explores how generative methods can play and meld with these traditional architectural and design forms.

metadata.name: Archiplex — Monochrome #12
metadata.description:
Archiplex Monochrome is a long form generative project, building on the short form Archiplex series. The Archiplex Monochrome algorithm is inspired by Brutalist architecture and design, where expressive forms emerge from the use of textures, materials and structures.

Archiplex Monochrome expands on these Brutalist design elements by floating the central structure of each piece and adding random light sources, introducing unpredictability and elevation to a traditionally structured and grounded art form.

"In this series my subject is the structure: formed yet formless, gravity-bound yet weightless, reflective yet light emitting, unmovable yet malleable."

metadata.name: Automata Bloke #12
metadata.description:
A bloke is like cellular automata, beautiful and complex, driven by simple rules governing their replication and destruction. 


All proceeds of this Parody AI Artwork to Girls Who Code and Cure Parkinson's

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #131
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Bright Circuits #244
metadata.description:
Looking at a motherboard seems like leaning over a busy city. Underneath the dense buildings (the components) runs at speed of electric fields an intricate transportation network that would drive any of our most practiced commuters crazy.
Designing circuit boards has been my job for a while. In addition to the technical approach I've come to deeply appreciate their aesthetical quality. The bond with generative art was striking to me.

The core code for "Bright Circuits" is a strict transcription of the rules at work when routing circuit tracks, i.e they can make 45° or 90° turns, they must respect a security gap between each other, and above all, they must never overlap. When the routing problem has no solution, we solve it by adding another layer of tracks, which communicates through soldered drill holes (Bright Circuits can have up to 3 layers).

At this point, the engineer in me got carried away by the art. As I was evolving from function to form, I started to imagine that the tracks where lifeforms driven by natural impulses, in an attempt to reach either freedom or a higher level of collective consciousness.
Despite the advent of AI we know that something that still differentiates the human from the machine is the ability to both feel, and conceptualise the feeling ; the free will and the ability for undeterministic decisioning.

Circuit tracks have managed to escape their boxed fate and arrange in shapes such as a circle, a heart, a skull (the components of a Vanity).
They now seek the experience of feeling. They have comprehended that feeling comes in a large palette of possibilities. Bright tracks are attracted to light (or positive moods), while dark tracks are running away from it (dark moods). The mix of both movements reflects the complexity of human feeling, which translates into a large variety of visual patterns.
Occasionally, they will go as far as outpassing their fundamental electronics rules and display a breakthrough creative mindset through features called "artistic rebellion" and "cartesian rebellion". "Bright Circuits" will also communicate through a pair of human words their clumsy attempt at feeling and doubting.


- press [s] in live view to export a PNG image file, between 9 and 8000 pixels wide.
- press [enter] to stop the animation and go straight to the result

Code in Vanilla Javascript + CSS

10% of the royalties are for minters

metadata.name: Shapes on a Plane #341
metadata.description:
“Shapes on a Plane” explores imaginary structures and worlds through simple shapes. It’s intended for small-scale print.

As a kid I was obsessed with Lego, Duplo, wooden building blocks... anything I could make something with.

I’d spend hours building things, imagining new worlds, new machines, new concepts, then i’d take them apart and create a whole new idea to explore.

To me, this piece to me is a reminder of that time - many days spent exploring ideas with those simple objects - no care for viability, for marketability, for audiences or business. Just pure fun.

Without this time in my life, I doubt I’d have found my passion for creating in the way I do today.
